{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"db32ec4c-b4ed-4316-9ad3-e761f13f1904","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four frameworks will report skipped tests distinctly from passed/failed, so they'll be visible in your test results.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"89909122-c253-46df-9064-81fcae6a36c5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attributes to skip tests with a reason message in MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question about .NET test frameworks. Let me check if any of my skills can help - the `dotnet-test-frameworks` skill seems relevant as it contains \"skip annotations\" information.","outputTokens":351,"requestId":"6804:2ED2CA:29BD829:2E3BEF1:69FD3A12"},"id":"b221ca93-bc96-4a70-88d9-0abb7b7b2497","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:19:22.643Z","parentId":"621feb62-481c-4145-a953-e75b01f599fc"}
